comments: Daniels (NOP) legally contests Gilgeous-Alexander's (OKC) jump shot, making "high-five" contact after the ball is released.
Dort (OKC) and Nance Jr. (NOP) briefly engage and separate during the rebound.
McCollum (NOP) initiates contact with Gilgeous-Alexander's (OKC) right arm before his gather, which affects his SQBR. This play should have been assessed as a personal foul.
McCollum (NOP) brings his arms forward and marginal contact occurs with Williams (OKC) as they briefly engage and quickly disengage off-ball.
Williamson (NOP) firms up over his right foot in Williams' (OKC) path and marginal lower-body contact occurs, which he does not deliver.
McCollum (NOP) establishes himself in Holmgren's (OKC) path and does not deliver illegal contact.
Hawkins (NOP) swipes down and delivers contact to Williams' (OKC) right arm, affecting his driving shot attempt.
Dort (OKC) initiates contact with Williamson's (NOP) arm, affecting Williamson's SQBR and causing him to lose control of the ball.
Dort (OKC) makes contact with Nance Jr.'s (NOP) head, which affects his ability to pursue the rebound.
Daniels (NOP) has a resting hand on Gilgeous-Alexander's (OKC) side during his driving shot attempt, and the contact is marginal.
Nance Jr. (NOP) cleanly blocks the shot attempt prior to when the ball reaches its apex.
Williams (OKC) is moving alongside Williamson's (NOP) path and marginal body contact occurs as they come together during the drive.
Holmgren (OKC) brings his hands toward Daniels (NOP) and marginal contact occurs as Daniels moves over the pick.
Gilgeous-Alexander (OKC) goes to, not through, Daniels' (NOP) space and marginal contact occurs as Gilgeous-Alexander (OKC) releases away during the drive.
Gilgeous-Alexander (OKC) establishes himself in Nance Jr.'s (NOP) path and does not deliver illegal contact.

Jones (NOP) legally contests Gilgeous-Alexander's (OKC) jump shot, making "high-five" contact after the ball is released. Jones closes out to the side and allows Gilgeous-Alexander space to land after legally defending the jump shot attempt.
Williams (OKC) commits a take foul on McCollum (NOP). The transition take foul rule does not apply to the last two minutes of either the fourth quarter or overtime.
After communicating with the Replay Center, it was determined that a common foul would be assessed.
